        <briefdescription>
<para>Get the inter-VM shared memory. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Note: This API is not supported for ivshmem-v2, as the R/W and R/O areas may not be mapped contiguously. For ivshmem-v2, use the ivshmem_get_rw_mem_section, ivshmem_get_output_mem_section and ivshmem_get_state APIs to access the shared memory.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dev</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the device structure for the driver instance </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>memmap</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A pointer to fill in with the memory address</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>the size of the memory mapped, or 0 </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
